'''Tenno Shrine''' (天皇神社) is a {{ill|shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|ja|滋賀県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{ill|Otsu City|ja|大津市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Geography ==
{{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|lt=JR|lt_ja=JR|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{ill|Wani Station|ja|和邇駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}} is located approximately 1.1 {{ill|kilometer|ja|キロメートル|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the southwest <ref name=":0">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.biwako-visitors.jp/spot/detail/158|title=天皇神社{{!}}滋賀県観光情報|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=びわこビジターズビューロー|date=2015-06-23}}</ref>, and a 10‐minute walk away <ref name=":1">{{Cite web|和書|url=http://nishioumi.ct-net.com/00-05.shtml|title=歴史散歩・和邇天皇神社　和邇祭り|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=京都新聞西近江販売所連合|year=2000|month=05}}</ref>. It is situated along the roadside of Ryūka Crossing (present‐day {{ill|Shiga Prefecture Route 311, Tokochu Shiga Line|ja|滋賀県道311号途中志賀線|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) {{Sfn|滋賀県教育委員会事務局文化財保護課|2019|p=20}}. It is about 5 minutes from {{ill|Kosai Road|ja|湖西道路|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|National Route 161|ja|国道161号|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) {{ill|Wani IC|ja|和迩インターチェンジ|lt=Wani IC|lt_ja=和邇IC|qq=draft|qq=draft}} <ref name=":2">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://otsu.or.jp/thingstodo/spot213|title=天皇神社|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=びわ湖大津観光協会}}</ref>.

== History ==
In 966 ({{ill|Kōhō|ja|康保|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3) the Gozu Tennō of {{ill|Yasaka Shrine|ja|八坂神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was returned, and it is said that it began under the name "Wani Gozu Tennōsha" {{Sfn|滋賀県教育委員会事務局文化財保護課|2019|p=20}}. The enshrinement is said to have been established in the late {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|lt=Kamakura|lt_ja=鎌倉|qq=draft|qq=draft}} <ref name=":0" />. In 1876 ({{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 9) it acquired its current name {{Sfn|滋賀県教育委員会事務局文化財保護課|2019|p=20}}. At that time, it became a village shrine <ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www.shiga-jinjacho.jp/ycBBS/Board.cgi/02_jinja_db/db/ycDB_02jinja-pc-detail.html?mode:view=1&view:oid=118|title=神社紹介　天皇神社（テンノウジンジャ）|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=滋賀県神社庁}}</ref>.

