'''Tenno Shrine''' (天皇神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|shrine]] located in [[:en:Shiga Prefecture|Shiga Prefecture]][[:en:Ōtsu|Otsu City]].

== Geography ==
[[:en:West Japan Railway Company|JR]][[:en:Wani Station|Wani Station]] is located approximately 1.1 [[:en:Kilometre|kilometer]] to the southwest <ref name=":0">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.biwako-visitors.jp/spot/detail/158|title=天皇神社{{!}}滋賀県観光情報|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=びわこビジターズビューロー|date=2015-06-23}}</ref>, and a 10‐minute walk away <ref name=":1">{{Cite web|和書|url=http://nishioumi.ct-net.com/00-05.shtml|title=歴史散歩・和邇天皇神社　和邇祭り|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=京都新聞西近江販売所連合|year=2000|month=05}}</ref>. It is situated along the roadside of Ryūka Crossing (present‐day {{ill|Shiga Prefecture Route 311, Tokochu Shiga Line|ja|滋賀県道311号途中志賀線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiga Prefecture Route 311, Tokochu Shiga Line|qq=}}) {{Sfn|滋賀県教育委員会事務局文化財保護課|2019|p=20}}. It is about 5 minutes from {{ill|Kosai Road|ja|湖西道路|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kosai Road|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 琵琶湖西縦貫道路}} ([[:en:Japan National Route 161|National Route 161]]) {{ill|Wani IC|ja|和迩インターチェンジ|lt=Wani IC|lt_ja=和邇IC|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wani IC|qq=}} <ref name=":2">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://otsu.or.jp/thingstodo/spot213|title=天皇神社|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=びわ湖大津観光協会}}</ref>.

== History ==
In 966 ([[:en:Kōhō|Kōhō]] 3) the Gozu Tennō of [[:en:Yasaka Shrine|Yasaka Shrine]] was returned, and it is said that it began under the name "Wani Gozu Tennōsha" {{Sfn|滋賀県教育委員会事務局文化財保護課|2019|p=20}}. The enshrinement is said to have been established in the late [[:en:Kamakura period|Kamakura]] <ref name=":0" />. In 1876 ([[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 9) it acquired its current name {{Sfn|滋賀県教育委員会事務局文化財保護課|2019|p=20}}. At that time, it became a village shrine <ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www.shiga-jinjacho.jp/ycBBS/Board.cgi/02_jinja_db/db/ycDB_02jinja-pc-detail.html?mode:view=1&view:oid=118|title=神社紹介　天皇神社（テンノウジンジャ）|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=滋賀県神社庁}}</ref>.

== Shrine Grounds ==
The main hall was constructed in [[:en:1324|1324]] (the first year of [[:en:Shōchū (era)|Shōchū]]) and has been designated as an [[:en:Important Cultural Property (Japan)|Important Cultural Property]] {{Sfn|滋賀県教育委員会事務局文化財保護課|2019|p=20}}. This main hall is one of only three examples of {{ill|Gabled Roof Construction|ja|切妻造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gabled Roof Construction|qq=}} in Shiga Prefecture (the others can be seen at {{ill|Ono Takamura Shrine|ja|小野篁神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Takamura Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and {{ill|Ono Dōfū Shrine|ja|小野道風神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Dōfū Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) <ref name=":0" />. The format of having three main halls with a rear worship space in a gabled structure is rare nationwide <ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www5.city.otsu.shiga.jp/kankyou/content.asp?key=0401000000&skey=207|title=大津のかんきょう宝箱　天皇神社（和邇中）|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=大津市環境部環境政策課}}</ref>. A characteristic feature from the time of its establishment is the remaining outline of a {{ill|Toad‐leg Motif|ja|蟇股|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toad‐leg Motif|qq=}} <ref name=":0" />. The roof is made of {{ill|Cypress Bark Roofing|ja|檜皮葺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Cypress Bark Roofing|qq=}} <ref name=":2" />.

== Annual Festival ==
The annual festival of Tenno Shrine, known as "Wani Festival" and sometimes referred to as "Goka Festival" <ref name=":1" />, is held by shrine officials from the Wani‐naka area and the districts of {{ill|Minamihama|ja|南浜|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamihama|qq=}}, {{ill|Nakahama|ja|中浜|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakahama|qq=}}, {{ill|Kitahama|ja|北浜|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitahama|qq=}}, {{ill|Imaju|ja|今宿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imaju|qq=}}, and {{ill|Takashiro|ja|高城|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashiro|qq=}} <ref name=":1" />. In the Minamihama district, on the early morning of the festival day, shrine officials depart from {{ill|Kimoto Shrine|ja|木元神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kimoto Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} to Tenno Shrine, and in the afternoon, portable shrines from other regions proceed to the lakeside resting area <ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www.rekihaku.otsu.shiga.jp/db/jiten/data/245.html|title=和邇祭{{!}}歴史事典|accessdate=2020-04-22|publisher=大津市歴史博物館}}</ref>. Its origin is attributed to the incident during [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]]'s assault on {{ill|Mount Hiei Arson (1571)|ja|比叡山焼き討ち (1571st year )|lt=Mount Hiei Arson|lt_ja=比叡山焼き討ち|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Hiei Arson (1571)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, when the portable shrine of [[:en:Hiyoshi Taisha|Hiyoshi Taisha]] fled to Tenno Shrine, which subsequently led to conflicts over its return <ref name=":1" />. It was once held annually on May 8, but nowadays, due to holiday scheduling, it is observed on the second Sunday of May each year <ref name=":1" />.

